                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d434">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51 War Credits/651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-07T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 7, 1934—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Department understands Greek Government instructed Bank of Greece on March 4
                    to transfer exchange necessary for payment of 27½ per cent of the interest on
                    its foreign loans for 1933–34. Please telegraph exact nature of this action and
                    whether provision for equal treatment with respect to service of 1929 loan from
                    United States Government is included.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
